column5: Anyone wanna fish the tri-city CSFL tounement this weekend?  I want to fish it, got the boat but have no co-angler.  Split entry, boat splits winnings.  I dont worry too much about fuel in the boat I can cover that.  I am leaving from Orangeville and dont know the tri-lakes at all. Someone who knows a little about the lake will be preferable.  Entry is 300 and it leaves from Rotary park in bridgenorth at 7 am and finishes at 3  Disclaimer: This will be my first CSFL

Good luck  I remember my first.  Blast off,is tricky.  Have a great day and hope you find someone that knows the lake. I dont,or would be all over this.  Ya,,you have my blood flowing.  Good luck and play safe.
lol I am so pumped up!!!  Thanks
Also you will need to conform to all CSFL rules and regs, as this is my first and my co-angler backed out last min I dont want to be violating any rules by doing this.
Well you probly didnt sleep much and are most likely on the road by now. LOL  Have fun Matt
Wish I seem this yesterday wpuld habe been all over. Get stuck again let me lnoe
Have fun. Tri Lakes has been fishing tough. Lot's of 1.5's.
